UML:Package.name: 1. Service providers will offer AAL services

UML:TaggedValue.value: Service providers or developers will upload AAL services.xml

Using web interface or ide plugin, authenticated service provider uploads a previously prepared file to the uStore, and then the system checks the file for correctness using built-in tools. According to the metadata of the service, and the properties of the service provider (he may be declared as trusted), the successfully checked service is published, or sent to an administrator for approval.
1. Service providers will offer AAL services
Service uploader uploads AAL service to uStore
Service providers may combine existing services into more complex solutions, which will be available as services as well, provided that they are not breaking any licenses.

Using tools or ide plugins, or any other means, the service provider defines all the required service metadata - names, descriptions, pictures, icons, categories, licenses, description of provided hardware and software components, courses, tutorials, pricing information, permissions to other users (can be service providers, developers or individual permission)

Using web interface or ide plugin, authenticated service provider uploads new version of file prepared in the "Preparing service for upload" use case to the Ustore for existing service. The system checks it accoding to "Service upload" use-case and saves it as new version of this service.
